maimai
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a duckshooter's shelter or hiding place usually made of (manuka) brushwood
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: 1845. R. Howitt, `Australia,' p. 103: -->1. (obs) a rough temporary bush shelter quickly put together from branches, etc. (Perhaps originally thought to refer to Maori shelters, thence in early colonial use, thence by trampers and mountaineers); a bush hut
